# ECUBE — Backend Addendum

Apply when touching Python backend code, API endpoints, services, models, repositories, or backend tests.

## API Rules

- Routers handle validation, role enforcement, and delegation only
- Services own business logic
- Endpoints must declare error responses
- No long-running synchronous work in endpoints
- No CPU-heavy work on the event loop
- Background tasks must use bounded thread pools

## Database and Model Rules

- PostgreSQL in production
- SQLite in-memory for tests
- Enum columns use `native_enum=False`
- JSON fields use SQLAlchemy `JSON` in models and PostgreSQL `JSONB` in migrations
- Index tables by project, status, and timestamps

## Domain Rules

- Drive lifecycle transitions must be atomic
- Drive FSM is `DISCONNECTED -> DISABLED -> AVAILABLE -> IN_USE`
- Background copy tasks must not starve the system

## Filesystem and Pagination

When touching browse, listing, or large-directory behavior:
- Use streaming iteration such as `os.scandir`
- Return `has_more` instead of computing full totals when possible
- Avoid memory-heavy directory materialization
- Do not materialize entire directories for paginated endpoints
- Do not globally sort very large directories unless explicitly required
- Do not introduce `O(n)` or `O(n log n)` work on each page request for large mount points

## Backend Test Expectations

When adding or changing endpoints, cover:
- role checks
- input validation
- pagination where relevant
- redaction
- derived fields
- error conditions
- edge cases